(193, NULL, 39, 1, '<p>For the function \\(f(x)=\\frac{x^3}{3}-6 x^2+3 x+3\\), the gradient is \\(-8\\)&nbsp;at two points.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">What are the values of the \\(x\\)&nbsp;- coordinates at these points?&nbsp;</p>', 'Both', 5, 5, 10, '<p>Solution:<br />\r\nFor gradient questions, differentiate first: $$ \\begin{aligned} f^{\\prime}(x) &amp; =3 \\times \\frac{x^2}{3}-2 \\times 6 x+3 \\\\ &amp; =x^2-12 x+3 \\end{aligned} $$ Next, letting \\(f^{\\prime}(x)=-8\\)&nbsp;and solving for \\(x\\): $$ \\begin{gathered} -8=x^2-12 x+3 \\\\ x^2-12 x+11=0 \\\\ (x-11)(x-1)=0 \\\\ \\therefore x=1 \\text { OR } 11 \\end{gathered} $$ Hence, the answer is \\(1\\)&nbsp;or \\(11\\)</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(-1\\) OR \\(11\\)</p>', '120', 'Hard', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-19 19:49:22', '2024-03-19 19:49:22'),
