(228, NULL, 47, 1, '<p>A chocolate factory&#39;s production each day is modelled by the equation: $$ N=3 t^2+2 t+2 $$ Where \\(N\\)&nbsp;is the amount of chocolate produced and \\(t\\)&nbsp;is the number of hours after the factory opens each day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At what rate is the factory producing chocolate 5 hours after opening today?</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 12, '<p>Solution:<br />\r\nWhen we think of rates, first consider the derivative: $$ \\frac{d N}{d t}=6 t+2 $$ Hence, five hours after opening when \\(t=5\\), the rate or \\(\\frac{d N}{d t}\\)&nbsp;will equal: $$ \\begin{aligned} \\frac{d N}{d t} &amp; =6(5)+2 \\\\ &amp; =32 \\end{aligned} $$ Thus, the factor will be producing 32 chocolates/hour 5 hours after opening!</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(87 \\text { chocolates/hour }\\)</p>', '60', 'Easy', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-20 09:05:09', '2024-03-20 09:05:09'),
