(256, NULL, 52, 1, '<p>A particle&#39;s displacement measured in \\(x\\) metres after \\(t\\) minutes is given by the equation: $$ x=6 t^2-5 t+6 $$ Which of the following is the equation for the velocity of this object?</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 13, '<p>The velocity of a particle is defined as the rate of change of its displacement. Hence \\(v=\\frac{d x}{d t}\\), so differentiating \\(x\\): $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\frac{d x}{d t}=12 t-5 \\\\ &amp; \\therefore v=12 t-5 \\end{aligned} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(v=6t-5\\)</p>', '60', 'Easy', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-20 09:48:54', '2024-03-20 09:48:54'),
