(260, NULL, 53, 1, '<p>An object&#39;s displacement measured in \\(x\\) metres after \\(t\\) seconds is given by the equation: $$ x=2 t^3+3 t^2-t+5 $$ Which of the following is the expression for the acceleration of this object?</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 13, '<p>First, differentiating \\(x\\) to find the velocity equation: $$ v=\\frac{d x}{d t}=6 t^2+6 t-1 $$ Then differentiating again to find the acceleration equation: $$ a=\\frac{d v}{d t}=\\frac{d^2 x}{d t^2}=12 t+6 $$ Hence, the expression for acceleration is: $$ a=12 t+6 $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(a=6t^2+6t-1\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-20 09:50:17', '2024-03-20 09:50:17'),
(261, NULL, 53, 2, '<p>An object&#39;s displacement measured in \\(x\\) metres after \\(t\\) seconds is given by the equation: $$ x=2 t^3+3 t^2-t+5 $$ Which of the following is the expression for the acceleration of this object?</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 13, '<p>First, differentiating \\(x\\) to find the velocity equation: $$ v=\\frac{d x}{d t}=6 t^2+6 t-1 $$ Then differentiating again to find the acceleration equation: $$ a=\\frac{d v}{d t}=\\frac{d^2 x}{d t^2}=12 t+6 $$ Hence, the expression for acceleration is: $$ a=12 t+6 $$</p>', 'correct', '<p>\\(a=12t+6\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-20 09:50:17', '2024-03-20 09:50:17'),
(262, NULL, 53, 3, '<p>An object&#39;s displacement measured in \\(x\\) metres after \\(t\\) seconds is given by the equation: $$ x=2 t^3+3 t^2-t+5 $$ Which of the following is the expression for the acceleration of this object?</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 13, '<p>First, differentiating \\(x\\) to find the velocity equation: $$ v=\\frac{d x}{d t}=6 t^2+6 t-1 $$ Then differentiating again to find the acceleration equation: $$ a=\\frac{d v}{d t}=\\frac{d^2 x}{d t^2}=12 t+6 $$ Hence, the expression for acceleration is: $$ a=12 t+6 $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(a=2t^2+3t-1\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-20 09:50:17', '2024-03-20 09:50:17'),
(263, NULL, 53, 4, '<p>An object&#39;s displacement measured in \\(x\\) metres after \\(t\\) seconds is given by the equation: $$ x=2 t^3+3 t^2-t+5 $$ Which of the following is the expression for the acceleration of this object?</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 13, '<p>First, differentiating \\(x\\) to find the velocity equation: $$ v=\\frac{d x}{d t}=6 t^2+6 t-1 $$ Then differentiating again to find the acceleration equation: $$ a=\\frac{d v}{d t}=\\frac{d^2 x}{d t^2}=12 t+6 $$ Hence, the expression for acceleration is: $$ a=12 t+6 $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(a=12t^2+6t\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-20 09:50:17', '2024-03-20 09:50:17'),
(264, NULL, 54, 1, '<p>A particle&#39;s velocity is given by the equation: $$ v=t^2-4 t-5 $$ Where \\(v\\) is the velocity of the particle and \\(t\\) is the time in seconds after the object begins moving&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At what time is the particle stationary?</p>', 'Both', 5, 5, 13, '<p>First, factorising our velocity equation: $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; v=t^2-4 t-5 \\\\ &amp; v=(t-5)(t+1) \\end{aligned} $$ A particle is considered stationary when \\(v=0\\), hence: $$ t=5 \\text { or } t=-1 $$ However, \\(t&gt;0\\) so: $$ &nbsp;\\therefore t=5 \\text { ONLY } $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(t=-1, 5\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-20 09:52:37', '2024-03-20 09:52:37'),
(265, NULL, 54, 2, '<p>A particle&#39;s velocity is given by the equation: $$ v=t^2-4 t-5 $$ Where \\(v\\) is the velocity of the particle and \\(t\\) is the time in seconds after the object begins moving&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At what time is the particle stationary?</p>', 'Both', 5, 5, 13, '<p>First, factorising our velocity equation: $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; v=t^2-4 t-5 \\\\ &amp; v=(t-5)(t+1) \\end{aligned} $$ A particle is considered stationary when \\(v=0\\), hence: $$ t=5 \\text { or } t=-1 $$ However, \\(t&gt;0\\) so: $$ &nbsp;\\therefore t=5 \\text { ONLY } $$</p>', 'correct', '<p>\\(t=5\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-20 09:52:37', '2024-03-20 09:52:37'),
(266, NULL, 54, 3, '<p>A particle&#39;s velocity is given by the equation: $$ v=t^2-4 t-5 $$ Where \\(v\\) is the velocity of the particle and \\(t\\) is the time in seconds after the object begins moving&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At what time is the particle stationary?</p>', 'Both', 5, 5, 13, '<p>First, factorising our velocity equation: $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; v=t^2-4 t-5 \\\\ &amp; v=(t-5)(t+1) \\end{aligned} $$ A particle is considered stationary when \\(v=0\\), hence: $$ t=5 \\text { or } t=-1 $$ However, \\(t&gt;0\\) so: $$ &nbsp;\\therefore t=5 \\text { ONLY } $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(t=2\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-20 09:52:37', '2024-03-20 09:52:37'),
(267, NULL, 54, 4, '<p>A particle&#39;s velocity is given by the equation: $$ v=t^2-4 t-5 $$ Where \\(v\\) is the velocity of the particle and \\(t\\) is the time in seconds after the object begins moving&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At what time is the particle stationary?</p>', 'Both', 5, 5, 13, '<p>First, factorising our velocity equation: $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; v=t^2-4 t-5 \\\\ &amp; v=(t-5)(t+1) \\end{aligned} $$ A particle is considered stationary when \\(v=0\\), hence: $$ t=5 \\text { or } t=-1 $$ However, \\(t&gt;0\\) so: $$ &nbsp;\\therefore t=5 \\text { ONLY } $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(t=-1, 2\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-20 09:52:37', '2024-03-20 09:52:37'),
(268, NULL, 55, 1, '<p>A particle moves such that its velocity at a time \\(t\\) seconds is given by \\(\\dot{x}=4 t^2-6 t\\).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\ni. Find when the particle is at rest&nbsp;<br />\r\n[1 mark]</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nii. Derive an expression for \\(\\ddot{x}\\)&nbsp;<br />\r\n[1 mark]<br />\r\n<br />\r\niii. What is the velocity when acceleration \\(\\ddot{x}=10 \\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}\\)?&nbsp;<br />\r\n[2 marks]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 13, '<p>i. Note that \\(\\dot{x}=v\\)&nbsp;<br />\r\nA particle is at rest when \\(\\dot{x}=0\\) $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; 4 t^2-6 t=0 \\\\ &amp; 2 t(2 t-3)=0 \\\\ &amp; \\therefore t=0 \\text { OR } \\frac{3}{2} \\end{aligned} $$ Hence, the particle is at rest when \\(t=0\\) and when \\(t=\\frac{3}{2}\\)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nii. Differentiating \\(\\dot{x}\\): $$ \\ddot{x}=8 \\mathrm{t}-6 $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>iii. When \\(\\ddot{x}=10\\): $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; 10=8 t-6 \\\\ &amp; 16=8 t \\\\ &amp; \\therefore t=2 \\end{aligned} $$ When \\(t=2\\): $$ \\begin{aligned} \\dot{x} &amp; =4(2)^2-6(2) \\\\ &amp; =16-12 \\\\ &amp; =4 \\mathrm{~ms}^{-1} \\end{aligned} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>$$t=0$$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>part ii:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$$\\ddot{x}=8t-6$$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>part iii:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$$\\dot{x}=4ms^{-1}$$</p>', '420', 'Hard', '4', 1, NULL, '2024-03-20 09:55:00', '2024-03-20 09:55:00');
